column3:
Describe fundamental biological concepts and principles, including:
a. evolution as a unifying concept of biology;
b. macro- and micro-evolutionary principles and mechanisms;
c. interactions between organisms and their environments across different scales of time and space and the processes that shape the diversity of life;
d. connections between structure and function from individual, population, community, and ecosystem perspectives including the influence of biotic and abiotic processes;
e. energy flow within and among biological systems;
f. sustainable balance of the health of organisms and ecosystems and value of biodiversity and its conservation on a local and global scale.
